recipeInstructions.text: Place avocado and guacamole spice mix in a medium bowl and mash until smooth. Transfer to a serving bowl.
Combine pineapple, onion and chopped coriander in a small bowl.

Heat oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Cook chicken, turning, for 3 minutes or until browned. Add spice mix (from kit) and add 1/2 cup water, and cook, stirring, for 3 minutes or until sauce thickens and chicken is cooked through.
Meanwhile, heat hard and soft tacos according to packet instructions.
Arrange hard and soft tacos on a platter. Fill with lettuce, chicken, pineapple salsa, guacamole and salsa (from kit). Sprinkle with extra coriander and serve.
